{"id":20237,"title":"Chromatographic separation of neodymium isotopes in human dental enamel for Thermal Ionisation Mass Spectrometry (TIMS) analysis","title_html":"Chromatographic separation of neodymium isotopes in human dental enamel for Thermal Ionisation Mass Spectrometry (TIMS) analysis","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png"},"doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.xzmfp46","doi_status":2,"uri":"chromatographic-separation-of-neodymium-isotopes-i-xzmfp46","type_id":1,"published_on":1549958142,"version_id":0,"created_on":1549911811,"categories":null,"creator":{"name":"Esther Plomp","affiliation":null,"username":"esther-plomp1","link":"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1016\/j.scijus.2019.02.001","image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/004.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/004.png"},"badges":[{"id":2,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/bronze.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/bronze.svg"},"name":"Author"}],"research_interests":null},"journal":null,"journal_name":null,"journal_link":null,"public":1,"has_versions":0,"link":"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1016\/j.scijus.2019.02.001","number_of_steps":6,"authors":[{"name":"Esther Plomp","affiliation":"Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam, the Netherlands","username":"esther-plomp1","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/004.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/004.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},{"name":"Richard Smeets","affiliation":"Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam, the Netherlands","username":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},{"name":"Janne Koornneef","affiliation":"Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam, the Netherlands","username":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},{"name":"Gareth Davies","affiliation":"Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam, the Netherlands","username":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"research_interests":null}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"steps":[{"id":707383,"guid":"06F70D002E3111E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","previous_id":707384,"previous_guid":"5FAA43E02E3111E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"06AB856D651148BE97CF9EB5C87A15A1","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Enamel collection"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"10F2EEE991DD45129C172F6938D45732","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Sample the enamel using a micro-drill fitted with a cleaned diamond-tipped rotary burr and blade (Minilor Perceuse). <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Burrs and blades should be cleaned before sampling teeth from different individuals to prevent contamination: <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Rinse with ethanol, 3 N HNO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">3<\/span><span> (Sigma-Aldrich Company Ltd) and ultrasound for 3 minutes, rinse with Milli-Q and ethanol. Let the burrs and blades dry on aluminium foil. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Clean the workspace with ethanol before sampling and prior to sampling different individuals.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">When sampling, ensure dentine separation from the enamel. Collect sampled enamel on aluminium foil prior to collecting the enamel in small glass bottles or cleaned eppendorf centrifuge tubes (6-7 N HCl  (Sigma-Aldrich Company Ltd) for > 7 days).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Combine the enamel from multiple teeth from the same individual if available.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><h2><\/h2><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF"},{"id":707384,"guid":"5FAA43E02E3111E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","previous_id":707386,"previous_guid":"E180F1702E3111E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C0A8449D0BE74BF8A64C0D767F8BBBF5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Tooth cleaning"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4731F7E336CE425094E572926D928AB2","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Leach the teeth for >8 hours in 30% H<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;vertical-align:sub;\">O<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span> (Sigma-Aldrich Company Ltd). Put the lids on the tubes but do not seal. Rinse the teeth with Milli-Q (>3 times) and dry on a hotplate at <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.  <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"4F8F39A02E3D11E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":50,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84"},{"id":707385,"guid":"A6F5E9C02E3111E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","previous_id":707383,"previous_guid":"06F70D002E3111E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8DE99B13105E4BAABEA2D0BDB0FFBC62","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Sample dissolution"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"87C80A5D7D87477481760B9977E4508B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Clean the PFA laboratory equipment: sub-boil in pro-analysis quality 7 N HNO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">3<\/span><span> and 6 N HCl for 2 hours each, followed by two leaching steps at <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>with (1) double distilled 6.5 N HCl (>5 days) and (2) 7 N HNO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">3<\/span><span>\/12 N HF (\u226540%Sigma-Aldrich Company Ltd) (>2 days).<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Prior to dissolving the enamel, add a <\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">150<\/span><span>Nd enriched spike (<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">143<\/span><span>Nd\/<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">150<\/span><span>Nd =142.93) to the sample to determine the Nd isotope concentration and Nd isotope composition of the same sample. Measure sample and spike bottle weight before and after addition of the spike to calculate the amount of spike added.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Dissolve the enamel in 3\u20136 mL 6.5 N HCl (> 12 hours). Dry (> 12 hours), nitrate with 10-30 drops of 14N HNO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">3, <\/span><span>let dry (> 4 hours) and re-dissolve in 3\u20136 mL 6.5 N HCl and 0.75\u20131.5 mL 14.0 N HNO (> 12 hours), depending on the sample weight. Dry (> 12 hours) and nitrate again before dissolving in 10 mL 2.0 N HNO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">3<\/span><span> (> 12 hours). Make sure there is no precipitate in the solution. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"85174BD02E3D11E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":125,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF"},{"id":707386,"guid":"E180F1702E3111E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6197DBF1164F459783096CE4D509EEB2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Tooth collection"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4BB41FCC8ACE480D81E09BD04CAD3279","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Collect the teeth in cleaned 50 mL plastic centrifuge tubes (rinsed >3 times with Milli-Q and 1 time with ethanol (Purity Grade: absolut, CHROMASOLV\u00ae, for high-performance liquid Chromatography)). <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Dry the teeth on a hotplate at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> (mind that plastic melts at higher temperatures).<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"44C0CE802E3D11E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":50,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF"},{"id":707408,"guid":"2DDF63F02E3511E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","previous_id":707385,"previous_guid":"A6F5E9C02E3111E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"75A813A2610E4892B7919F0DEC8297BA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Chemical separation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"41725F06D557418B93AC3A185EB19854","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">REE are seperated from the matrix using TRU-resin protocol (Step 5), followed by an Ln-resin protocol (step 6) to seperate Nd from the REE fraction. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">The required TRU-resin volume depends on the sample size: 0.75 mL resin for samples up to 550 mg and 1.3 mL resin for samples >550 mg, using modifield columns (Pasteur pipettes).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Ultrasonicate the samples for 30 minutes and centrifuge for 4 minutes at 4000 rpm before loading onto the columns.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Cleaning of the columns:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">6 mL 2 N HF<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">6 mL Milli-Q<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>6 mL 2 N HNO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">3<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">6 mL Milli-Q<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Precondition:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>6 mL 2 N HNO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">3<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Prefraction (25 CV): <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>19 or 33 mL 2 N HNO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">3<\/span><span> (depending on 0.75 or 1.3 mL TRU-resin)<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>\tSample load: 10 mL 2 HNO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">3<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>\tWash: 9 or 23 mL 2 N HNO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">3<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">REE extraction (10 CV) :<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">8 or 14 mL Milli-Q<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF"},{"id":707414,"guid":"1B0DB4402E3811E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","previous_id":707408,"previous_guid":"2DDF63F02E3511E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B7382E34498249B68071470D19A576B6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation for Ln columns"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2BC1AF1B60F34499B8D1E626D2B855CF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Dry the REE fraction (overnight) on a hotplate at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Dissolve the REE fraction in 2 mL 0.165 N HCl for Nd separation using standard Ln 0.74 mL resin columns (PE-column and 35 \u00b5m PE-frit):<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Cleaning of columns day 1:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>4 mL 6 N HNO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">3<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">4 mL 2 N HF<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">4 mL Milli-Q<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">4 mL 6-7 N HCl<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">1 mL 0.165 N HCl<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">(store columns overnight in 0.165 N HCl in centrifuge tubes (10 mL, cleaned with 6-7 N HCl for > 7 days))<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Cleaning day 2: <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2 mL 6-7 N HCl<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2 mL Milli-Q<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Precondition: <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2 mL 0.165 N HCl<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Prefraction: <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">9-11 mL 0.165 N HCl (depending on how long the Ln-resin is in use)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">\tSample load: 1-2 mL 0.165 N HCl<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">\tSample wash: 7-10 mL 0.165 N HCl<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Nd extraction: <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">4 mL 0.3 N HCl<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Dry samples down at<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span> and nitrate with 10 drops of 14 N HNO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">3. <\/span><span>Close the vial and place on a hotplate at <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> for 2 hours. Tap down the condensation drops every 30 minutes. Open the vial and dry down down at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">for TIMS analysis. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"5C4B6B002E3D11E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":120,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"79BDB7B02E3D11E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","order_id":3,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":110,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"69E467D02E3D11E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","order_id":4,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":120,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"70D5BFD02E3D11E9B56F03C9CF6D38B5","order_id":5,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":110,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF"}],"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Protocol for sample collection, dissolution and chromatographic separation of neodymium isotopes in human dental enamel for Thermal Ionisation Mass Spectrometry (TIMS) analysis.<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1549958142}